This equals: $P(\text{at least one drug has } \geq 9 \text{ successes})$

Using inclusion-exclusion:
$P(\max \geq 9) = P(X_1 \geq 9) + P(X_2 \geq 9) + P(X_3 \geq 9)$
$- P(X_1 \geq 9 \text{ and } X_2 \geq 9) - P(X_1 \geq 9 \text{ and } X_3 \geq 9) - P(X_2 \geq 9 \text{ and } X_3 \geq 9)$
$+ P(X_1 \geq 9 \text{ and } X_2 \geq 9 \text{ and } X_3 \geq 9)$

