$P(X = 9) = \binom{10}{9}(0.7)^9(0.3)^1 = 10 \times 0.7^9 \times 0.3 = 10 \times 0.040353607 \times 0.3 = 0.121060821$

$P(X = 10) = \binom{10}{10}(0.7)^{10}(0.3)^0 = 0.7^{10} = 0.028247554$

$P(X \geq 9) = 0.121060821 + 0.028247554 = 0.149308375$

For independent events:
$P(X_1 \geq 9 \text{ and } X_2 \geq 9) = P(X_1 \geq 9) \times P(X_2 \geq 9) = (0.149308375)^2 = 0.022293001$

Similarly for all three pairs:
$P(\text{any two} \geq 9) = 0.022293001$ (same for all three pairs)

$P(X_1 \geq 9 \text{ and } X_2 \geq 9 \text{ and } X_3 \geq 9) = (0.149308375)^3 = 0.003329099$

By inclusion-exclusion:
$P(\max \geq 9) = 3(0.149308375) - 3(0.022293001) + 0.003329099$

$= 0.447925125 - 0.066879003 + 0.003329099$

$= 0.384375221$

